{"lemma":"مَذْهَبٌ","slug":"مَذْهَبٌ","root":"ذ.ه.ب","root_slug":"ذ-ه-ب","root_link":"/words/roots/ذ-ه-ب","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":false},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":6,"pos_tags":["adj","noun","verb"],"has_etymology":true,"sense_count":15},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n14123"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D9%85%D9%8E%D8%B0%D9%92%D9%87%D9%8E%D8%A8%D9%8C"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"noun","gloss":"verbal noun of ذَهَبَ (ḏahaba) (form I)","tags":["form-of","noun-from-verb"]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"going, leaving, departure"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"sect, denomination, doctrine, school of jurisprudence or thought","examples":[{"text":"اَلْمَذْهَب الشَّافِعِيّ","english":"the Shafi'i school of jurisprudence"},{"text":"اَلْمَذْهَب السُّنِّيّ","english":"the Sunni sect"}]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"way out, escape"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"procedure, policy, manner"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"doctrine, teaching, belief, ideology, opinion, view"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"faith"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"religion, creed"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"course, school"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"way, movement, orientation"},{"pos":"adj","gloss":"active participle of ذَهَّبَ (ḏahhaba)","tags":["active","form-of","participle"]},{"pos":"adj","gloss":"gilded"},{"pos":"adj","gloss":"active participle of أَذْهَبَ (ʔaḏhaba)","tags":["active","form-of","participle"]},{"pos":"adj","gloss":"gilded"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to cause to split into sects"}]},"etymology":{"source":"wiktextract","text":"Verbal noun and noun of place from the verb ذَهَبَ (ḏahaba, “to go”).\n\nDerived from the active participle of the verb ذَهَّبَ (ḏahhaba, “to gild”), denominal verb from ذَهَب (ḏahab, “gold”).\n\nDerived from the passive participle of the verb ذَهَّبَ (ḏahhaba, “to gild”), denominal verb from ذَهَب (ḏahab, “gold”).\n\nDerived from the active participle of the verb أَذْهَبَ (ʔaḏhaba, “to gild”), denominal verb from ذَهَب (ḏahab, “gold”).\n\nDerived from the passive participle of the verb أَذْهَبَ (ʔaḏhaba, “to gild”), denominal verb from ذَهَب (ḏahab, “gold”).\n\nDenominal verb from مَذْهَب (maḏhab, “sect”)."},"ipa":["/mað.hab/","/mu.ðah.hib/","/mu.ðah.hab/","/muð.hib/","/muð.hab/","/mað.ha.ba/"],"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n14123","headword_ar":"مَذْهَبٌ","root":"*hb","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"is an inf. n.: (JK, A, K:) ―         -b2-  and also signifies"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A place of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"*ahaAb","text_ar":"ذَهَاب"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"going,"},{"kind":"text","text":"&c.]: and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a time thereof."},{"kind":"text","text":"(JK.) ―         -b3-  [Also"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A place to which one goes:"},{"kind":"text","text":"see an ex. voce"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maHoDarN","text_ar":"مَحْضَرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". ―         -b4-  And hence,] (tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A place to which one goes for the purpose of satisfying a want of nature; a privy;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA;)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"i. q."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mutawaD~aA^N","text_ar":"مُتَوَضَّاٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (JK, A, K, TA;) in the dial. of the people of El-Hijáz. (JK, A, TA.) ―         -b5-  [Also"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A way by which one goes"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"goes away."},{"kind":"text","text":"―         -b6-  And hence, as in several exs. in the first paragraph of this art.,] (tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A way, course, mode,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"manner, of acting"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"conduct"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the like:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Msb, K, TA:) (tropical:)  ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a way that one pursues in respect of doctrines and practices"},{"kind":"text","text":"in religion &c.; and particularly"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a way of believing, opining, thinking,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"judging;"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a belief, a creed, a persuasion, a doctrine, an opinion, a tenet,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a body of tenets"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"articles of belief;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K, TA;)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"an opinion"},{"kind":"text","text":"in, or respecting, religion; and, accord. to Es-Sarakustee,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"an innovation"},{"kind":"text","text":"in religion: (Msb:) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"*ahobN","text_ar":"ذَهْبٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"signifies the same. (JK, TA.) [The pl. is"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ma*aAhibu","text_ar":"مَذَاهِبُ"},{"kind":"text","text":". Hence,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"*awuw ma*aAhibu","text_ar":"ذَوُو مَذَاهِبُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Persuasions,"},{"kind":"text","text":"as meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"persons holding particular tenets in religion"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the like."},{"kind":"text","text":"] ―         -b7-  Also (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Origin:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Ks, Lh, K:) so in the sayings,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maA yudoraY lahu A^ayona ma*ohabahu","text_ar":"مَا يُدْرَى لَهُ اَيْنَ مَذْهَبَهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"laA yudoraY lahu","text_ar":"لَا يُدْرَى لَهُ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ma*ohabN","text_ar":"مَذْهَبٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", i. e. (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"It is not known whence is his origin."},{"kind":"text","text":"(Ks, Lh, TA.)"}],"source_refs":["JK","A","K","Msb","TA","Ks","Lh"]}]},"classical_definitions":null}